lm — local-models toolkit (all on your machine, no cloud)

COMMANDS
  lm q "..."           quick local LLM — answers, macOS commands, titles
  lm imagine "..."     local image generation (Flux/Qwen on the GPU)
  lm warm on|off       warm-model toggle (snappy on / zero-idle off)
  lm status            server + warm + models at a glance
  lm doctor            smoke-check the whole toolkit (server, models, venv, PATH)
  lm timeline [N]      merged q + imagine history, one timeline

EXAMPLES
  $ lm q cmd "free up port 3001"
  $ lm q "how do I check disk usage"
  $ lm imagine --enhance "a cozy reading nook"
  $ lm imagine -m qwen "a sign reading OPEN"
  $ lm imagine critique out.png "a moody forest"
  $ lm warm on        # then q + imagine --enhance are sub-second

